<comment id="12015" author="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:03:24 +0900"><ol> <li>“Content Version processing” supports Standard / Long / Multi-dialogue, but the docs do not define what these modes change in UI or generation behavior.</li> <li>“Global and per-item settings” is clear, but per-item scope is not: per POI only, or per POI + per language?</li> <li>“Voice model”, “Director Context”, and “Script Enhancement limits” are mentioned as controls, but allowed values and validation rules are not specified.</li> <li>“Persist with FireCMS/Backend” is ambiguous on save timing: auto-save on change, save on generate, or explicit save action?</li> <li>“Processed one by one per POI” conflicts a bit with “batch” language generation elsewhere; needed execution order is unclear for multi-language runs.</li> </ol> </comment>
